**Yes — nonconvex optimization is increasingly linked to cryptography, especially in privacy-preserving distributed systems. Recent academic work explores how optimization algorithms can be adapted to run securely over encrypted data or with differential privacy guarantees. To study this area, you’ll need strong foundations in optimization theory, cryptography, and applied mathematics.**

