**If you already know nonconvex optimization but have zero background in cryptography, the best starting point is structured lecture notes from introductory cryptography courses. These cover the mathematical foundations (probabilistic polynomial time, negligible functions, hardness assumptions) and basic primitives (encryption, signatures, pseudorandomness) that are essential before tackling research papers in privacy-preserving optimization.**

